The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	 City tennis umpire Abhishek Mukherjee will be the first Indian to officiate in the US Open I am happy It was my childhood dream, Mukherjee, who has officiated in the Australian Open and Wimbledon, said on Wednesday. This year he was also selected for the Hopman Cup in Australia and the New Zealand pro circuit in Hamilton and Wellington, also for the first time. He has also been invited to officiate in the Beijing Olympic Games in August, 2008.           
	 East Bengal beat Mohun Bagan 4-2 in the ONGC Bengal Table Tennis Premier League at the SAI on Wednesday. While Soumyajit Sarkar and Sourav Chakraborty won two matches for Mohun Bagan, East Bengals Poulami Ghatak and Sougata Sarkar won their respective singles. East Bengal won both their doubles matches.                       
	 East Bengals Brazilain striker Edmilson Marques, who reached the city early morning, was present at the club practice on Wednesday. According to a club official, the forward is likely to play against Peerless SC on July 30.       
	He is in good shape and seemed in good touch too, coach Manoranjan Bhattacharjee said after practice.                
	FOOTBALL: CFL Premier Division, East Bengal vs Railway FC (Salt Lake Stadium, 3.30 pm)       
	GOLF: The Telegraph Cup at RCGC      
	TABLE TENNIS: ONGC Premier League (SAI, 2.30 pm)                                                                                                                                                                     
